title: Cafe ProFusion
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Ovo, International, Beer/Wine, Take-out, Fusion, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Self-described as "a little gourmet hole in the wall," this cafe offers dishes with inspirations from Middle Eastern, Mediterranean, Indian, Thai, and Korean cuisine. The menu is small and clearly-labeled as half vegan and completely gluten-free, with occasional vegetarian specials. Dishes include gingered red lentils, roasted garlic hummus, and New Delhi garbanzo bean stew. Opened summer 2012.
